            {
              "text": "Secure External + Efficient Internal Communication",
              "level": 0
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Google Shape;64;p14",
          "shape_type": 17,
          "left": 863625,
          "top": 1125700,
          "width": 7738200,
          "height": 4265400,
          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "text": "External: gRPC over HTTPS via Tyk",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Internal: gRPC over H2C (plain HTTP/2)",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Common in Kubernetes environments",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "TLS termination at ingress",
              "level": 1
            },
            {
              "text": "Plain HTTP inside cluster",
              "level": 1
            },
            {
              "text": "gRPC client \u2194 Tyk Gateway (HTTPS) \u2194 gRPC Server (H2C)",
              "level": 0
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        "\"This example demonstrates a common pattern in Kubernetes deployments \u2014 securing external traffic with TLS while using HTTP/2 Cleartext (H2C) for internal service-to-service communication. Tyk terminates the TLS connection, then forwards gRPC traffic to the upstream server using H2C, enabling efficient bidirectional streaming.\""
      ]
    },
