          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "text": "A gRPC server (e.g. route_guide)",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Exposed at localhost:10000, TLS disabled",
              "level": 1
            },
            {
              "text": "A gRPC client (sample or your app)",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "A valid certificate for HTTPS",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Tyk Gateway and Dashboard",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Set flush_interval = 1 ms in tyk.conf",
              "level": 0
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        "\"Before configuring Tyk, make sure your gRPC server is running with TLS disabled. This is intentional so that we can connect over H2C. Also, the Tyk Gateway\u2019s flush_interval should be set to 1 millisecond to ensure data is forwarded immediately, which is critical for bidirectional streaming.\""
      ]
    },
