          "paragraphs": [
            {
              "text": "Protocol: HTTPS",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Upload SSL certificate",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Custom domain: tyk.com",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Listen path: /routeguide.RouteGuide",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "RouteChat method will be used (bidirectional)",
              "level": 0
            },
            {
              "text": "Target URL: h2c://localhost:10000",
              "level": 0
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "notes": [
        "\"In the Tyk Dashboard, create a new API definition. Set the protocol to HTTPS so clients can connect securely. Then, point the target URL to the internal gRPC server using the h2c:// prefix. This instructs Tyk to forward requests using HTTP/2 without TLS, ideal for intra-cluster calls.\""
      ]
